headline: The AI Selloff Has Covid Parallels, Say Analysts. These Sectors Can Survive.
summary: European markets have held up slightly better than their U.S. counterparts in recent weeks but the nerves still seem to be creeping in.  Morgan Stanley  analysts estimated that the market is ascribing a risk of AI disruption to around 24% of the weight of the MSCI Europe index, up from just 4% a month ago.  Concerningly, the analysts said they “see parallels to the rapidly shifting market psychology around the COVID pandemic,” though they noted it’s not their base case.
